sequenceDiagram
    participant O as Orchestrator (parent)
    participant P as Pro (process)
    participant J as Judge (process)
    participant C as Con (process)
    participant CLI as claude -p (+WebSearch)

    Note over O: one ping = Pro turn + Con turn, both routed through the Judge
    O->>P: act(context = opponent_last + running summary)
    P->>CLI: invoke(skill_pro, prompt) via Gatekeeper.guard
    CLI-->>P: argument + web-source citations
    P-->>O: ProtocolMessage (pro -> judge)
    O->>J: relay(pro_msg, recipient = con)
    J-->>O: ProtocolMessage (judge -> con)
    O->>C: act(context = Pro's argument)
    C->>CLI: invoke(skill_con, prompt) via Gatekeeper.guard
    CLI-->>C: rebuttal + web-source citations
    C-->>O: ProtocolMessage (con -> judge)
    O->>J: relay(con_msg, recipient = pro)
    J-->>O: ProtocolMessage (judge -> pro)
    Note over O: repeat for pings_per_side rounds (default 10)
    O->>J: verdict(transcript)
    J->>CLI: invoke(skill_judge, transcript)
    CLI-->>J: JSON verdict (winner + differential scores)
    J-->>O: Verdict (no tie, justified)
